            "summary": "Malicious actors are using fake Microsoft Office extensions on SourceForge to steal crypto; Kaspersky discovered a malicious listing named \"officepackage\" containing malware called ClipBanker that replaces copied crypto wallet addresses. The malware sends device info to hackers and can delete itself if already installed. Small file sizes and interface in Russian targeting Russian-speaking users are red flags. Kaspersky warned against downloading software from untrusted sources. 90% of victims were in Russia, with 4,604 affected users between January and March. The firm also highlighted new malware targeting crypto users, urging caution. Threat Fabric found malware tricking Android users for seed phrases. Other news includes Bitcoin potentially reaching $70K and a crypto-funded SpaceX flight.",
