            "summary": "Cryptocurrencies faced a decline on Tuesday due to U.S.-China trade war concerns. Bitcoin fell by 3.32% to $76,504.63, Ethereum dropped 5.16% to $1,469.57, and Dogecoin decreased by 4.11% to $0.1427 by 8:30 p.m. ET. Bitcoin initially hit $80,000 but later dropped below $76,000. Ethereum also saw a decline to $1,427.05 from a short-lived rally. Bitcoin's market dominance increased to 62.7%, while Ethereum's decreased to 7.2% from over a year ago. $271 million in long positions were liquidated due to the slump. There is a risk of liquidation for over $950 million in shorts on Binance if Bitcoin rebounds to $80,000. Bitcoin's Open Interest decreased by 2.08% in the last 24 hours and over 16% from late March highs. Bitcoin's Long/Short ratio also fell in the last 24 hours.",
